description.narrative: The objective of the Project is to assist the Borrower's Project Cities in enhancing: (i) the performance and quality of their existing urban transport infrastructure in terms of mobility, access, and safety; (ii) the efficiency and effectiveness of their urban public transport and road maintenance services; and (iii) the responsiveness of their urban transport systems to the needs of population without access to private motorized vehicles.

condition.narrative: Furnish to Bank by 02/15 of each yr beginning 02/15/07 a proposed action plan for carrying out its Respective Parts of theProject,including the financing plan and detailed budget arrangements
Proj Impl Ent shall cause Proj City to notify the Bank of changes in legal stat of SOE bus co, granting of bus route or networkconces. of more than 3 yrs & tranf from govt ownership of bus fixed infr
Proj Impl Ent shall cause ea Proj City to furnish an annual report to Bank by 12/15 of ea yr beg. 12/15/06 describing procurementcompleted in such yr for non-Bank fin. rd maint contracts in Proj City
Project Impl Ent shall cause each Proj City to arrange an annual mtg chaired by its respective Rd Safety Com in Oct of each yrstarting 10/2006 to review records of rd safety & traffic flows
Project Implementing Entity shall cause each Project City to conduct a public survey using public participatory process on impacts&benefits of Project by 6/302008 and 06/30/11 respectively
